        "title": "Using BufferedReader to print out data separated by commas",
        "body": "<p>I need to print out values from certain columns in a csv file.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jPryB.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/jPryB.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Below is an example of the data. There is a comma in one field and I have tried putting in the commas like; <code>System.out.println(&quot;\\&quot;&quot; + b[0] + &quot;\\&quot;,\\&quot;&quot; +b[4] + &quot;\\&quot;,\\&quot;&quot;+ b[6] + &quot;\\&quot;&quot;);<\/code> But this confuses the code and mixes up the commas within the csv file value.<\/p>\n<p>Code looks like this;<\/p>\n<pre><code>&quot;Van&quot;,&quot;Truck&quot;,&quot;&quot;Car&quot;,&quot; new&quot;&quot;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>I want to display the data like this:<\/p>\n<pre><code>&quot;Car,new&quot;, &quot;Van&quot;, &quot;Truck&quot;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><strong>Note the comma at the end of Car<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Below is my code. How can I get it to ignore print out and ignore the comma after Car instead of putting double quotes around it?<\/p>\n<p>thanks in advance<\/p>\n<pre><code>         BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(sr));\n          String splitBy = &quot;,&quot;;\n          String line = br.readLine();\n          while((line = br.readLine()) != null){\n            String[] b = line.split(splitBy);\n            System.out.println(&quot;\\&quot;&quot; + b[0] + &quot;\\&quot;,\\&quot;&quot; +b[4] + &quot;\\&quot;,\\&quot;&quot;+ b[6] + &quot;\\&quot;&quot;);\n          }\n          br.close();\n        }\n      }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
